snippet.textDisplay: Sajjad Ali composed the song for his album Soni Lagdi, released by Sound Master in 1999.  The singer/composer has been active in the music industry for last three decades, while living in the UAE for a good portion of that time. This, somehow, has alienated him from the local Pakistani music industry. The artist has been protective to his compositions like a purist and turned down remixing and revisiting offers (Rafay Mehmood Jan. 2017). His on-line music lessons are available under the title, "How to Sing: Basic Vocal Training" on Master Class. Sajjad enjoys an enviable discography with hits ranging from PTV compositions to film music, not to forget, his albums. His recent collaboration was with Bohemia (Though Bohemia's contribution was less then a minute, most of the time he shows his hipster's moves around Sajjad Ali in the video). And with his talented daughter Zaw Ali, a film maker turned musician.
